Privacy Policy

Last updated: July 19, 2026

This Privacy Policy describes how SansCarki (“we,” “us,” or “our”) collects, uses, and shares information when you use the SansCarki mobile application (the “App”).

By using the App, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.

Information We Collect
Account information If you sign in with Google, we may collect your Google account identifier, email address, display name, and profile photo as provided by Google Sign-In and Firebase Authentication.

Gameplay and profile data We store information related to your use of the App, such as points, completed tasks, badges, game progress, activity history, and similar in-app progress data. This data may be stored locally on your device and/or in cloud services such as Google Firebase (including Cloud Firestore).

Photos you choose to provide If you upload or take a photo as proof for a daily task, that photo may be stored on your device and/or processed as needed to provide the related feature. We do not sell these photos.

Device and advertising identifiers The App may collect device information and advertising identifiers (such as the Android Advertising ID) to show ads and measure ad performance through Google AdMob.

Locally stored data The App may store preferences and temporary state on your device using local storage (for example, SharedPreferences), such as settings and daily spin/ad status.

How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect to:

create and manage your account
provide, operate, and improve the App’s features (daily tasks, fortune wheel, games, progress tracking)
sync your progress across sessions when you are signed in
show advertisements, including rewarded and interstitial ads
maintain security, prevent abuse, and fix technical issues
comply with legal obligations
Third-Party Services
The App uses third-party services that may collect information according to their own privacy policies, including:

Google Firebase (Authentication, Cloud Firestore, and related services)
Google Sign-In
Google AdMob (advertising)
Google Play In-App Updates (where applicable)
These providers may process data such as account details, device identifiers, usage data, and advertising identifiers. We encourage you to review their privacy policies.

Google’s privacy policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy

Advertising
The App displays ads through Google AdMob. Ads may use advertising identifiers and related device information to deliver and measure advertisements. You may be able to limit ad personalization through your device settings (for example, reset or opt out of personalized ads on Android).

Data Sharing
We do not sell your personal information.

We may share information only:

with service providers who help us operate the App (such as Google Firebase and Google AdMob)
if required by law, legal process, or to protect rights, safety, and security
in connection with a business transfer (for example, merger or acquisition), if applicable
Data Retention
We retain account and progress data for as long as your account remains active or as needed to provide the App. Local data remains on your device until you delete the App or clear app data. You may request deletion of your account-related data by contacting us.

Data Security
We take reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your information. However, no method of transmission or storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

Children’s Privacy
The App is not directed to children under 13 (or the minimum age required in your country). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us so we can delete it.

Your Rights and Choices
Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, update, or delete your personal information. You can:

sign out of your account within the App
delete the App and/or clear local app data
manage Google account permissions
contact us to request account or data deletion
International Transfers
Your information may be processed and stored on servers located outside your country of residence, including through Google’s infrastructure. By using the App, you acknowledge that your information may be transferred to and processed in such locations.

Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will post the updated version in the App or on the related store listing page and update the “Last updated” date. Continued use of the App after changes means you accept the updated Privacy Policy.
